ZH: 我雇了一个保镖来保护我的家人。
EN: I hired a bodyguard to protect my family.

ZH: 那个明星总是有很多保镖围绕着他。
EN: That celebrity always has many bodyguards around him.

ZH: 这家很有钱的人雇了一支专业的保镖队伍。
EN: This wealthy person hired a professional bodyguard team.

ZH: 他被派去做一个政府官员的保镖。
EN: He was assigned to be a bodyguard for a government official.

ZH: 这位大富豪的保镖身手不凡，能够解决突发危险情况。
EN: The bodyguard of this millionaire is extraordinary and can handle unexpected dangerous situations.

ZH: 我朋友是一名职业保镖，每天都在负责名人的安全。
EN: My friend is a professional bodyguard and is responsible for the safety of celebrities every day.

ZH: 这位保镖身高两米，给人一种强大的安全感。
EN: This bodyguard is two meters tall and gives people a strong sense of security.

ZH: 他的保镖技能包括武装格斗和紧急医疗。
EN: His bodyguard skills include armed combat and emergency medical care.

ZH: 这位保镖对于安保领域有丰富的经验。
EN: This bodyguard has extensive experience in the field of security.

ZH: 年轻的明星刚出道就找了一名保镖来保护自己。
EN: The young celebrity hired a bodyguard to protect himself as soon as he debuted.

ZH: 这家贵族的保镖队伍严格进行了选拔和培训。
EN: The bodyguard team of this noble family underwent strict selection and training.

ZH: 保镖对于名人的安全至关重要。
EN: Bodyguards are crucial for the safety of celebrities.

ZH: 他的保镖跟随在他身后，时刻保持警惕。
EN: His bodyguard follows closely behind him, always alert.

ZH: 那位亿万富翁给了他的保镖一大笔奖金，以示感谢。
EN: The billionaire gave his bodyguard a large bonus as a token of gratitude.

ZH: 这位保镖的反应速度非常快，能够迅速应对危险。
EN: This bodyguard has a very fast reaction speed and can respond quickly to danger.

